r the new final display requirement.\n    b. When `!tb_match` is true and `stats1.errors == 0`, record `$time` as the first error time.\n    c. Replace the existing `final` block with the new required logic.\n    d. Implement the combinational mismatch display logic inside the `always @(posedge clk, negedge clk)` block (or where the mismatch is detected), triggered only on the *first* error, to show inputs/outputs/expected values at that time.\n\n**Syntax Advice:**\n- Ensure all signals in the interface and testbench use `logic` type for consistency, following the golden testbench's trend.\n- The verification assignment `assign tb_match = ( { out_ref } === ( { out_ref } ^ { out_dut } ^ { out_ref } ) );` is functionally equivalent to `assign tb_match = ( out_ref === out_dut );` since XORing with the same value twice results in the original value ($A \text{ XOR } B \text{ XOR } B = A$). However, since the requirement is to FOLLOW the golden testbench if it contradicts the spec, I must keep the existing verification logic.\n- The complex structure of the golden testbench (including `stimulus_gen` and `RefModule`) must be preserved exactly.\n\n**Refining Mismatch Display:**\nFor combinational logic, the check for mismatch happens synchronously with the clock edge in the golden testbench's `always @(posedge clk, negedge clk)`. Therefore, the display showing inputs/outputs should occur within this clocked block when the first mismatch is detected, capturing the state at that clock edge.",
